     Jed wants you to stay.

02:46.633 --> 02:48.801
     Are you gonna help him
       keep me prisoner?

02:51.371 --> 02:53.972
  Are you gonna slide my food
        under the door?

02:54.040 --> 03:00.779
               ♪♪

03:00.847 --> 03:02.514
        It's what Colin
        would've wanted.

03:02.583 --> 03:04.048
    Colin hated his brother.

03:04.118 --> 03:07.051
    He'd want me as far away
   from here as I could get.

03:07.053 --> 03:11.723
               ♪♪

03:11.792 --> 03:14.659
I'll come back and get your
plate when you're done.

03:14.661 --> 03:18.863
               ♪♪

03:18.865 --> 03:23.067
               ♪♪

03:23.069 --> 03:24.469
         Smurf's dead.

03:24.538 --> 03:26.738
            I know.

03:26.807 --> 03:28.941
         We're sitting
       on a lot of gold.

03:29.009 --> 03:30.475
      We need to fence it.

03:30.544 --> 03:33.011
   I'm not taking on any new
      business right now.

03:33.080 --> 03:35.079
    We're not new business.

03:35.081 --> 03:38.082
      My relationship was
      with Smurf, not you.

03:38.084 --> 03:39.017
      What does that mean?

03:39.086 --> 03:41.553
       Means Smurf leaves
          a big void.

03:41.622 --> 03:44.623
Someone's gonna fill it.
I'll wait to see who.

03:44.691 --> 03:46.691
So you're just gonna leave money
         on the table?

03:46.761 --> 03:49.027
        I trusted Smurf.

03:49.096 --> 03:50.362
       I don't know you.

03:50.430 --> 03:52.697
            This is
    a relationship business.

03:52.767 --> 03:55.500
     Smurf made the deals,
       handled the money.

03:55.569 --> 03:57.836
            You boys
       were only muscle.

04:04.711 --> 04:06.244
        Those homeschool
         prepper freaks

04:06.313 --> 04:08.180
        are gonna figure
       out where we live.

04:10.985 --> 04:12.451
           They gonna
         come after us?

04:12.519 --> 04:14.753
             Maybe.

04:17.524 --> 04:19.325
   See if the old guy's dead?

04:21.060 --> 04:22.928
           He's dead.

04:29.136 --> 04:32.538
           Hey. So...

04:36.677 --> 04:38.811
      Uh, we need to have
           a funeral

04:38.879 --> 04:40.813
         or a memorial
         or something.

04:40.881 --> 04:42.514
             What?

04:43.750 --> 04:47.019
 All eyes are on us right now.

04:47.087 --> 04:48.687
     We're still the Codys.

04:48.755 --> 04:50.689
     Everyone needs to know
       that we're strong,

04:50.757 --> 04:51.824
     with or without Smurf.

04:51.892 --> 04:53.758
   We need to let people know
        that we're here

04:53.760 --> 04:54.759
  and that we're in business.

04:54.829 --> 04:57.295
          No funeral.

04:57.364 --> 05:00.165
   We're sitting on a million
     dollars worth of gold,

05:00.234 --> 05:02.034
          and we have
       nobody to move it.

05:02.102 --> 05:04.169
     I just spoke with Gia.
     She's not interested.

05:04.238 --> 05:05.570
           [ Scoffs ]

05:05.572 --> 05:07.840
   We'll find another fence.

05:10.977 --> 05:12.444
           -We done?
          -We're done.

05:14.048 --> 05:16.749
       Lose the glasses.
     You're not John Gotti.

05:29.663 --> 05:31.396
           Passports.

05:31.465 --> 05:33.632
   Make sure you drill Adrian
        on the new name.

05:34.935 --> 05:36.502
       In case they ask.

05:37.938 --> 05:39.138
         Yeah. Thanks.

05:41.275 --> 05:44.142
           "Thanks"?

05:44.211 --> 05:46.245
           That's it?

05:48.482 --> 05:50.014
             What?

05:50.016 --> 05:51.784
           Am I ever
      gonna see you again?

05:55.021 --> 05:58.290
I'm gonna get us set up down
there, and then, I don't know.

05:58.358 --> 06:00.492
    Man, I got a baby, man.

06:00.561 --> 06:02.026
          I need you.
        -No, you don't.

06:02.096 --> 06:03.161
           Yes, I do.

06:03.230 --> 06:04.463
           You don't.

06:06.567 --> 06:08.433
       You got something
       that's yours now.

06:08.502 --> 06:10.235
        You and Renn are
     great together, okay?

06:10.304 --> 06:11.303
         Listen to me.

06:11.371 --> 06:13.638
        You're gonna be
     a great father, okay?

06:13.640 --> 06:15.908
       I don't doubt that
         for a second.

06:15.976 --> 06:19.043
      Dude, we can finally
       do things our way.

06:19.045 --> 06:20.512
       The way that we've always
             talked about doing.

06:20.581 --> 06:22.247
What do you want me to do, man?
         What do you --

06:22.316 --> 06:24.716
   What am I supposed to do?

06:24.785 --> 06:27.185
       I can't let Adrian
         go to prison.

06:27.254 --> 06:28.787
       I just -- I can't.

06:37.798 --> 06:40.265
          I gotta go.

06:40.267 --> 06:42.267
      [ Jeep door opens ]

06:48.809 --> 06:50.542
       [ Engine starts ]

06:50.611 --> 06:56.815
               ♪♪

06:56.883 --> 07:03.288
               ♪♪

07:03.290 --> 07:04.823
    At least we have to have
         a memorial --

07:04.891 --> 07:07.159
       We never discussed
        bringing Gia in.

07:07.227 --> 07:09.294
       Smurf connected me
        with Gia before.

07:09.296 --> 07:11.696
        Yeah, I know, J.
  You've always got an angle.

07:11.766 --> 07:14.366
       You've always got
           an angle.

07:14.434 --> 07:17.302
       You want to be one
         of us so bad.

07:18.973 --> 07:21.774
     You think you can run
          the family?

07:21.842 --> 07:24.109
           You think
       you can be Smurf?

07:25.379 --> 07:27.980
       You're a leech, J.

07:28.048 --> 07:29.514
     None of us trust you.

07:29.516 --> 07:32.584
         You've been lying to us
    since the day you showed up.

07:34.054 --> 07:38.524
            You've got 24 hours.
     Pack your shit and get out.

07:41.195 --> 07:42.661
            Get out!

07:42.729 --> 07:44.463
       [ Plate clatters ]

07:44.531 --> 07:46.865
      Get out of my house.

07:49.403 --> 07:52.438
       [ Andrew crying ]

07:58.945 --> 08:00.745
          He wants you
        to pick him up.

08:00.815 --> 08:02.981
      [ Crying continues ]

08:04.751 --> 08:06.351
       Come here, honey.

08:06.420 --> 08:08.220
        [ Andrew calms ]

08:08.288 --> 08:10.622
    Shh, shh, shh, shh, shh.
          You're okay.

08:10.691 --> 08:14.092
             Good.
       You're okay, Andy.

08:14.161 --> 08:16.695
      You gotta hold 'em.
      Let them smell you.

08:16.763 --> 08:17.762
       First couple days
         are important.

08:17.832 --> 08:20.132
       Yeah, I hold them.

08:24.038 --> 08:26.505
  Can't believe she can sleep
       through all that.

08:26.573 --> 08:29.441
     He's feisty, isn't he?

08:29.510 --> 08:32.678
       Looks pissed off.
       Don't you, Andrew?

08:35.115 --> 08:36.581
      [ Andrew whimpers ]

08:36.582 --> 08:38.984
     Jed keeps the car keys
        in the gun safe.

08:41.388 --> 08:43.621
     He thinks I don't know
        the combination.

08:46.260 --> 08:47.592
        [ Keys rattle ]

08:47.661 --> 08:54.466
               ♪♪

08:54.535 --> 08:57.402
         He's in town.

08:57.471 --> 08:59.738
       What's he gonna do
            to you?

08:59.806 --> 09:05.210
               ♪♪

09:05.279 --> 09:06.545
        [ Keys rattle ]

09:08.615 --> 09:10.449
    You should come with us.

09:12.619 --> 09:15.353
       What about my cash
          and my gun?

09:15.422 --> 09:17.956
        You need to go.
              Now.

09:18.024 --> 09:21.293
               ♪♪

09:21.362 --> 09:23.228
     Thanks a lot, asshole.

09:23.297 --> 09:25.363
   Screw you! Piece of shit!

09:25.432 --> 09:28.233
Man: Yeah? Try showing up
for a shift once in a while.

09:28.302 --> 09:30.069
           [ Sighs ]

09:35.842 --> 09:37.709
             Jesus.

09:37.778 --> 09:39.578
       What, do you work
           here now?

09:39.646 --> 09:42.247
    [ Scoffs ] Not anymore.

09:42.316 --> 09:44.583
       What do you want?
              Huh?

09:44.651 --> 09:45.684
          Mike's out.

09:47.988 --> 09:49.588
             What?

09:49.656 --> 09:51.790
          Mike is out.

09:51.858 --> 09:54.126
     He's looking for you.

09:56.530 --> 09:58.663
    They were leaning on me.
    I was dope sick, and --

09:58.732 --> 10:00.132
            I think
     you're a piece of shit

10:00.200 --> 10:01.700
          who's earned
     what's coming to you.

10:03.270 --> 10:05.938
      But I don't want my baby's
          father back in prison,

10:06.006 --> 10:08.273
      so you stay the hell
         away from him.

10:08.275 --> 10:13.612
               ♪♪

10:13.680 --> 10:16.949
   I'm with Andrew Cody now,
       so tell him that.

10:17.017 --> 10:19.351
         Smurf's dead.

10:19.420 --> 10:21.686
      Cody don't mean shit
            anymore.

10:21.755 --> 10:27.359
               ♪♪

10:27.428 --> 10:28.394
       [ Lighter clicks ]

10:33.834 --> 10:35.033
        Can I help you?

10:35.102 --> 10:38.704
Yeah, I have envelopes for
Deran, Craig, and Julia Cody.

10:38.772 --> 10:39.971
             Julia?

10:40.040 --> 10:41.039
             Yeah.

10:41.041 --> 10:42.608
           That's me.

10:44.912 --> 10:47.179
           Thank you.
            -Mm-hmm.

10:55.523 --> 10:57.589
       [ Brakes squeal ]

10:57.657 --> 10:59.158
      [ Engine shuts off ]

11:01.595 --> 11:03.696
        [ Baby crying ]

11:18.678 --> 11:20.612
           Hey, uh...

11:20.680 --> 11:22.814
        What you doing?

11:22.883 --> 11:25.283
       It's getting good
           out there.

11:25.352 --> 11:28.354
      [ Crying continues ]

11:28.422 --> 11:30.622
    Did you get the diapers?

11:35.629 --> 11:39.431
               ♪♪

11:39.499 --> 11:43.101
               ♪♪

11:43.103 --> 11:45.404
         [ Bag unzips ]

11:46.240 --> 11:47.439
        [ Lock clicks ]

11:47.507 --> 11:52.510
               ♪♪

11:52.580 --> 11:57.583
                ♪♪

11:57.651 --> 12:02.654
               ♪♪

12:02.722 --> 12:05.591
           [ Sighs ]

