               ♪♪

12:20.340 --> 12:26.211
                ♪♪

12:26.280 --> 12:28.079
        ♪ I wasn't born,
        I was detached ♪

12:28.148 --> 12:29.948
      What's all that shit
         doing outside?

12:29.950 --> 12:31.483
      Oh, it's for Smurf.

12:31.551 --> 12:33.885
Sorry, dude. I didn't even know
       your mom was sick.

12:33.954 --> 12:34.886
         Yeah, thanks.

12:34.955 --> 12:36.088
            Yo, hey.

12:36.156 --> 12:38.724
  Uh, some guy in the office,
        waiting for you.

12:40.428 --> 12:42.160
What do you mean, there's
somebody in the office?

12:42.229 --> 12:44.162
      Who's in the office?

12:44.164 --> 12:45.831
            I dunno.

12:45.899 --> 12:47.765
          Is it a cop?

12:47.767 --> 12:50.202
    Doesn't look like a cop.

12:59.246 --> 13:00.479
              Hey.

13:04.384 --> 13:06.051
           Hey, man.

13:06.120 --> 13:08.554
             Jesus.

13:19.066 --> 13:20.766
        Excuse me. Pope?

13:22.202 --> 13:23.068
             Yeah?

13:23.137 --> 13:25.003
      I brought your boys
           a lasagna.

13:25.005 --> 13:26.404
             Okay.

13:26.474 --> 13:29.274
I'm so sorry about your mom.
She was a great woman.

13:29.343 --> 13:31.477
         So was so kind
        and thoughtful.

13:33.013 --> 13:34.746
           I'm sorry.
          Who are you?

13:34.815 --> 13:36.348
        Marjorie. Grant.

13:36.416 --> 13:38.751
 Smurf and I have been friends
           for years.

13:40.287 --> 13:42.888
         Uh, I've never
         heard of you.

13:42.956 --> 13:45.023
       She helped me out
         with my rent.

13:45.092 --> 13:47.625
 That's just the kind of person
            she was.

13:47.695 --> 13:49.762
          So generous.

13:51.565 --> 13:53.231
             Right.

13:53.233 --> 13:55.300
    And what were you doing
            for her?

13:55.369 --> 13:57.769
          This, that.

13:57.838 --> 13:58.904
             Right.

13:58.972 --> 14:01.306
She always had it to me
on the first of the month.

14:01.375 --> 14:03.241
   We'll get you your money.

14:03.243 --> 14:04.376
        Thank you, dear.

14:04.444 --> 14:07.579
       You boys take care
         of yourselves.

14:07.647 --> 14:09.314
         Oh, hey, uh...

14:09.383 --> 14:12.918
  We -- We're throwing a party
        this afternoon.

14:12.986 --> 14:17.189
          A memorial.
 Sort of a send-off for Smurf.

14:19.193 --> 14:21.560
      You should come by.

14:22.796 --> 14:25.397
     Tell whoever you want.

14:25.465 --> 14:27.599
     I'll make some calls.

14:27.667 --> 14:32.670
               ♪♪

14:32.740 --> 14:36.175
      I brought the, uh --
      the money I owe you.

14:37.545 --> 14:41.146
          Most of it.
       Well...some of it.

14:41.215 --> 14:45.483
And I'll have the rest in,
uh...a couple weeks.

14:45.553 --> 14:46.818
          What are you
         talking about?

14:46.887 --> 14:48.019
     The money I borrowed.

14:48.088 --> 14:49.955
         You borrowed?

14:50.023 --> 14:52.358
             Okay.
      Don't be like that.

14:52.426 --> 14:54.426
           All right?

14:54.494 --> 14:57.695
       I'm trying to get
           sober now.

14:57.697 --> 14:59.631
      Believe me, stealing
        from my own kid,

14:59.699 --> 15:01.967
          that was...
        my rock bottom.

15:02.036 --> 15:05.037
         Sure it wasn't the time
           when you kidnapped me

15:05.105 --> 15:07.573
       and then you sold me back
    to Smurf for a bag of smack?

15:07.641 --> 15:10.075
   Is that what she told you?

15:13.180 --> 15:14.446
           All right.

15:14.514 --> 15:17.115
   I'm assuming you found out
          Smurf died.

15:17.184 --> 15:18.250
             Yeah.

15:18.318 --> 15:20.185
        That's probably
        why you're here.

15:20.254 --> 15:22.320
       What do you need,
  a place to stay? What is it?

15:22.389 --> 15:24.657
            -No. No.
       -Out of my chair.

15:27.327 --> 15:29.327
           [ Sighs ]

15:29.396 --> 15:31.163
        [ Keys clatter ]

15:34.334 --> 15:36.802
           I'm guaranteeing you,
       within two weeks or less,

15:36.870 --> 15:38.303
      I'll have the rest.

15:41.141 --> 15:44.476
         Listen, man...

15:44.544 --> 15:46.745
      I'm all you got now.

15:46.814 --> 15:48.414
        And vice versa.

15:51.419 --> 15:53.018
   I'm doing this, you know?

15:53.086 --> 15:55.287
      I'm -- I'm gonna get
        clean and sober,

15:55.355 --> 15:58.424
        I'm gonna stay that way,
          and I'm gonna be here.

15:58.492 --> 16:00.558
           You know?
      I'm gonna be around.

16:00.628 --> 16:02.227
           For real.

16:02.296 --> 16:05.363
Yeah, well, you got shitty
timing 'cause I'm out of here.

16:05.365 --> 16:06.898
   I can come back tomorrow.
         I don't care.

16:06.967 --> 16:08.834
         I mean, to me, whenever
           you want to sit down.

16:08.902 --> 16:10.102
            No, no.
     You missed your shot.

16:10.170 --> 16:12.370
I'm not gonna be here tomorrow
or the day after that,

16:12.440 --> 16:13.939
        week after that.

16:14.775 --> 16:17.375
        Where you going?

16:17.377 --> 16:19.177
     Taking a trip, or...?

16:19.179 --> 16:20.912
   Get out of my bar, Billy.

16:20.981 --> 16:22.380
        You can tell me
            where --

16:22.382 --> 16:24.316
      I said get the hell
         out of my bar.

16:27.721 --> 16:30.388
 [ The Grizzled Mighty's "Cabin
         Fever" plays ]

16:30.458 --> 16:31.490
           [ Sighs ]

16:35.329 --> 16:37.997
   ♪ I like the status quo

16:38.799 --> 16:40.999
         You work here
         or something?

16:41.068 --> 16:43.401
     Are you following me?

16:43.403 --> 16:46.004
            I'm your
       guardian angel, J.

16:46.006 --> 16:48.073
       What do you want?

16:48.142 --> 16:50.342
         Smurf's dead.

16:50.410 --> 16:52.678
           What now?

16:52.746 --> 16:55.114
      Pope kicked me out.

16:56.216 --> 16:58.550
   He thinks I got you high.

16:58.618 --> 17:01.153
     I wonder where he got
        that idea from.

17:02.556 --> 17:04.455
     Who's Pamela Johnson?

17:07.761 --> 17:10.029
        I-I don't know.
              Why?

17:12.098 --> 17:14.199
         Really? Okay.

17:17.971 --> 17:19.771
      That's Smurf's will.

17:19.839 --> 17:22.773
           She sent three copies
      to the house this morning.

17:22.843 --> 17:26.845
   One each to Deran, Craig,
           and Julia.

17:26.847 --> 17:28.513
            My mom?

17:28.582 --> 17:31.249
       She gives Deran and Craig
          just enough to get by.

17:31.251 --> 17:33.785
 Same for Julia, which I assume
        will go to you.

17:33.854 --> 17:37.156
    Everything else goes to
    some woman named Pamela.

17:37.991 --> 17:39.257
        Even the house.

17:39.326 --> 17:41.459
        What about Pope?

17:41.529 --> 17:43.128
    Gets a small trust fund.

17:43.197 --> 17:46.398
    Deran is his trustee...

17:46.466 --> 17:49.401
   in case Pope survived her.

17:49.469 --> 17:51.603
       Has he seen this?

17:51.671 --> 17:53.472
              No.

17:57.878 --> 17:59.344
     What's in it for you?

17:59.413 --> 18:01.180
       I'll be with Pope.

18:03.283 --> 18:06.151
   You're stronger with them.

18:06.220 --> 18:07.586
            So am I.

18:16.964 --> 18:18.030
           Hey, Pam.

18:18.098 --> 18:19.498
            Janine.

18:22.570 --> 18:24.436
       I had the babies.

18:24.504 --> 18:25.437
            Babies?

18:25.505 --> 18:27.373
            Mm-hmm.

18:27.441 --> 18:29.675
             Twins.
        Boy and a girl.

18:34.582 --> 18:36.314
        [ Baby fusses ]

18:36.383 --> 18:38.516
         They're cute.

18:38.518 --> 18:40.118
       What do you want?

18:40.187 --> 18:42.588
    You said we should work
           together.

18:42.656 --> 18:44.722
           Here I am.

18:44.724 --> 18:46.724
   Uh, those kids don't look
           like they

18:46.726 --> 18:48.193
         are more than
       a couple days old.

18:48.262 --> 18:50.662
       Should you even be
        walking around?

18:50.730 --> 18:52.264
           I'm fine.

18:54.402 --> 18:55.434
         Where's Colin?

18:58.739 --> 19:00.239
             Dead.

19:03.277 --> 19:04.810
           I'm sorry.

19:06.280 --> 19:08.413
   And what about the others?

19:08.482 --> 19:12.451
           Uh, yeah.
     I can't go back there.

19:14.554 --> 19:17.756
      [ Breathes deeply ]

19:19.760 --> 19:21.893
     I'm looking for work.

19:21.962 --> 19:23.629
      You just had twins.

19:23.697 --> 19:24.896
             -Yeah.
             -Okay.

19:24.965 --> 19:28.233
           We'll talk
       in a couple weeks.

19:28.302 --> 19:29.835
       [ Car door opens ]

19:29.903 --> 19:31.937
   What am I supposed to eat
           till then?

19:36.243 --> 19:38.110
           [ Sighs ]

19:47.387 --> 19:48.821
             Fine.

19:55.129 --> 19:58.063
Is that enough to get you to
wherever Jake is holed up?

19:58.132 --> 20:01.166
       Whatever you did,
     Jake'll take you back.

20:07.475 --> 20:09.742
    I'm gonna pay you back.

20:12.079 --> 20:13.945
          It's a gift.

20:14.014 --> 20:17.282
          I don't like
         to owe people.

20:17.351 --> 20:20.418
             Um...

20:20.420 --> 20:22.954
       Do you have a gun
         I can borrow?

20:23.023 --> 20:25.658
           [ Laughs ]

20:36.604 --> 20:38.070
           Hey, Jake!

20:38.138 --> 20:40.472
         Jesus, Janine!

20:40.540 --> 20:41.807
       Is Manny in there?

20:41.875 --> 20:44.276
        No, he's shacked up with
      some chick in Bakersfield.

20:44.344 --> 20:45.611
         It's just me.

20:45.679 --> 20:48.313
          Will you put
   the gun down now, please?

20:57.357 --> 20:59.291
    It was hard to find you.

20:59.359 --> 21:00.492
   I've been bouncing around.

21:00.560 --> 21:02.828
Yeah. Well, we've been sleeping
 on the beach a few nights.

21:03.563 --> 21:05.030
             "We"?

21:05.098 --> 21:07.633
       Andrew and Julia.

21:07.701 --> 21:09.701
          I had twins.

21:09.769 --> 21:12.570
            No shit.

21:12.572 --> 21:15.174
        Where are they?

21:27.721 --> 21:29.187
       [ Babies fussing ]

21:29.256 --> 21:32.358
 Well, you comin' in or you want
    to keep sleeping on a beach?

21:39.333 --> 21:42.600
 Billy: There was this lifeguard
           down at Cassidy Beach

21:42.670 --> 21:45.471
       back in the day --
       Good-lookin' guy.

21:45.539 --> 21:47.405
      Borrowed some money
          from Smurf.

21:47.475 --> 21:49.074
    She told him to pay up.

21:49.143 --> 21:53.812
    And, uh...I guess he thought
           she was full of shit.

21:53.881 --> 21:57.815
  God, remember how sexy she was
             back in those days?

21:57.817 --> 21:59.351
            Uh-huh.

21:59.419 --> 22:01.753
  Yeah, I think the guy's name
           was Jimmy.

22:01.822 --> 22:04.422
  Yeah, I think it was Jimmy.
  She wakes me up, she's like,

22:04.424 --> 22:06.224
       "Listen, we gotta
       go talk to Jimmy."

22:06.226 --> 22:09.561
           So I'm figuring I got
        to whack the guy around,

22:09.629 --> 22:12.964
  impress the shit out of Smurf,
             she'll be grateful.

22:13.033 --> 22:14.700
        Win-win for me.

22:14.768 --> 22:16.702
        We're walking up
          on the guy.

22:16.770 --> 22:19.505
       She grabs the guy
          by the hair,

22:19.573 --> 22:22.708
    drags him down to the water,
      sticks a gun in his mouth.

22:22.776 --> 22:23.975
            Oh, no.

22:24.044 --> 22:27.312
    Yeah. And I'm going, "Smurf,
           baby, it's 800 bucks.

22:27.381 --> 22:29.181
            Relax."

22:29.249 --> 22:31.449
           She goes,
   "It's not about the money.

22:31.519 --> 22:33.585
   It's about the principle."

22:33.653 --> 22:35.787
             Yeah.
        Her reputation.

22:35.856 --> 22:37.356
             Right?
             -Yeah.

22:39.793 --> 22:42.094
      What do you think's
  gonna happen to those boys?

22:44.264 --> 22:45.997
     Oh, I don't know, man.

22:46.066 --> 22:47.665
         I don't know.

22:47.735 --> 22:51.937
       You have no idea the shit
   that went down in that house.

22:52.005 --> 22:54.672
         She really --
   She messed those kids up.

22:54.674 --> 22:57.943
     You know? Not my kid.
        My kid's great.

22:58.011 --> 23:01.346
      I got the good one.

23:01.415 --> 23:04.149
       Yeah, my kid's, you know,
          good-lookin', smart --

23:04.218 --> 23:06.352
      He owns his own bar.

23:06.420 --> 23:08.286
       I mean, he figured
      shit out, you know?

23:08.288 --> 23:09.955
          [ Chuckles ]

23:10.023 --> 23:12.290
      You ever meet Craig?

23:12.292 --> 23:15.694
Smurf told me if I ever went
near him, she'd kill me.

23:17.097 --> 23:18.597
        I believed her.

23:19.833 --> 23:22.500
             Yeah.

23:22.570 --> 23:24.036
       He's big and dumb.

23:24.104 --> 23:25.170
           [ Scoffs ]

23:25.239 --> 23:27.573
          No offense.
    I mean, he's a good guy.

23:27.641 --> 23:29.575
           You know?
       Got a good heart.

23:29.643 --> 23:31.543
          He's funny.
        You'd like him.

23:34.848 --> 23:37.049
       You gonna tell him
          who you are?

23:46.460 --> 23:47.725
          -Hey, Craig.
             -Hey.

23:47.727 --> 23:48.994
      Sorry for your loss.

23:49.062 --> 23:50.662
     [ Wolfie's Just Fine's
    "Break My Back" plays ]

23:50.731 --> 23:52.130
       ♪ Break my back

23:52.132 --> 23:57.135
    ♪ I got a ravenous lover
          in repose ♪

23:57.137 --> 23:58.403
       ♪ Take it back

23:58.472 --> 23:59.938
         Hey, yo, man.

24:00.007 --> 24:01.006
           What's up?

24:01.074 --> 24:03.541
     Sorry about your mom.
        She's the best.

24:03.611 --> 24:05.277
            Thanks.

24:05.345 --> 24:07.479
       We only hooked up
         that one time,

24:07.547 --> 24:09.081
   but it was a good memory,
           you know?

24:11.819 --> 24:14.720
     All right, man, well,
       thanks for coming.

24:17.557 --> 24:19.458
         -Sorry, Craig.
             -Yeah.

24:21.295 --> 24:24.830
           [ Sighs ]
         Nice turnout.

24:31.038 --> 24:33.539
  Craig: Who the hell are all
         these people?

24:46.186 --> 24:49.321
      You see those guys?
          That group?

24:49.389 --> 24:50.856
            -Uh-huh.
             -Cops.

24:50.924 --> 24:52.724
   Was she paying them, too?

24:52.792 --> 24:54.860
    Either that, or they're here
         to rub our faces in it.

24:54.928 --> 24:57.663
     You wanna go ask them?

24:57.731 --> 25:01.933
  Yeah, well, see that burnout
          over there?

25:02.002 --> 25:04.602
    He just told me how much
   he enjoyed banging Smurf.

25:04.604 --> 25:05.471
             Jesus.

25:05.539 --> 25:08.607
Yeah, seems like
a lot of people loved her.

25:13.613 --> 25:15.881
           Holy shit.

25:15.949 --> 25:17.249
             What?

25:19.219 --> 25:20.752
         What the hell
      are you doing here?

25:20.821 --> 25:23.088
Hey, man, sorry about your mom.
         Hey, man. Hey.

25:23.157 --> 25:24.289
          -Come here!
           -Come on.

25:24.358 --> 25:27.425
               ♪♪

25:27.427 --> 25:28.560
             What?

25:28.628 --> 25:30.696
            Nothing.

25:33.233 --> 25:35.701
            -Really?
     -You got 10 seconds --

25:35.769 --> 25:38.504
   10 seconds to get out of here
             before I shoot you.

25:38.572 --> 25:40.772
          I just came
       from seeing Deran.

25:40.841 --> 25:43.075
           All right?
 And I wanted to come see you.

25:48.582 --> 25:49.581
             What?

25:49.649 --> 25:52.918
I -- I recognize now --
and this is not easy

25:52.986 --> 25:55.120
  for me to say when you have
       a gun in my face.

25:55.189 --> 25:58.724
You know, I c-could've done some
things differently, okay?

25:58.792 --> 26:02.528
So, you know, I'm sorry
for some of the shit

26:02.596 --> 26:05.130
       that I did to you
      when you were a kid.

26:05.199 --> 26:06.664
             Some?

26:06.666 --> 26:09.201
 Some of the shit you did to me
       when I was a kid?

26:09.269 --> 26:11.136
   Some of it you had comin',
         let's face it.

26:11.205 --> 26:12.404
       What is this shit?

26:12.472 --> 26:14.072
  What, are you making amends
       or some bullshit?

26:14.141 --> 26:15.741
          Yeah. I am.

26:15.809 --> 26:19.511
    I'm three months sober.
           So, yeah.

26:21.815 --> 26:23.281
           [ Scoffs ]

26:23.350 --> 26:24.550
         Let's just put
      the gun away, dude.

26:24.618 --> 26:26.952
I'm not -- You're not gonna
shoot me at your mom's memorial.

26:27.020 --> 26:28.520
            Come on.

26:30.357 --> 26:32.057
          Good. Okay?

26:34.762 --> 26:36.228
         Listen, man...

26:36.296 --> 26:38.096
      I think I did a lot
      of that stuff to you

26:38.165 --> 26:40.098
     when you were a kid --
       I did it 'cause...

26:40.100 --> 26:43.035
I was jealous, you know?
You were the love of her life.

26:44.972 --> 26:46.371
         She hated me.

26:46.440 --> 26:48.240
She didn't hate you.
What are you talking about?

26:48.308 --> 26:50.508
   She worshipped the ground
         you walked on.

26:50.510 --> 26:51.910
      You came from Colin.

26:51.912 --> 26:53.178
         Okay? He died.

26:53.247 --> 26:55.713
     He didn't get a chance
       to disappoint her

26:55.715 --> 26:57.182
      like the rest of us.

26:58.786 --> 27:00.185
           You know?

27:00.254 --> 27:02.888
       I heard Colin was
    a crazy son of a bitch.

27:06.059 --> 27:08.360
      Sounds about right.

27:11.932 --> 27:14.666
      Deran know you were
       coming over here?

27:14.735 --> 27:17.603
Yeah, I went over there to talk
 to him, but he didn't --

27:17.671 --> 27:19.537
  he didn't feel like talking,
       which is a bummer.

27:19.539 --> 27:21.673
         But, you know,
       he was too busy...

27:21.742 --> 27:23.875
       packing or leaving
         or something.

27:23.944 --> 27:25.343
             What?

27:25.345 --> 27:26.544
     Maybe he's just taking
        his boyfriend up

27:26.614 --> 27:28.280
        to Palm Springs
    for the weekend, but --

27:28.348 --> 27:30.282
            Leaving?

27:30.350 --> 27:32.151
  That's what it looked like.

27:36.957 --> 27:39.491
         Are you going
          over there?

27:39.559 --> 27:40.426
       [ Engine starts ]

27:40.494 --> 27:42.127
      I'll come with you.

27:45.165 --> 27:47.099
      Nice talking to you.

28:04.718 --> 28:11.457
               ♪♪

28:11.525 --> 28:13.292
    What're you doing here?

28:18.466 --> 28:21.700
     You knew Adrian was talking
        to the cops, didn't you?

28:24.538 --> 28:26.772
  You've been protecting him.
           I know it.

28:29.543 --> 28:30.542
      Well, it's not true.

28:30.610 --> 28:32.210
    Well, I didn't think so.

28:32.212 --> 28:33.545
      Then Billy shows up.

28:33.613 --> 28:35.280
            He says
      you're leaving town.

28:35.349 --> 28:37.349
          So it starts
         to make sense.

28:37.417 --> 28:39.551
        The Colby shit.

28:39.619 --> 28:44.556
               ♪♪

28:44.624 --> 28:50.362
               ♪♪

28:50.430 --> 28:53.098
          They got him
    on a drug charge, okay?

28:53.167 --> 28:55.167
               ♪♪

28:55.235 --> 28:57.569
      They threatened him
         with 20 years.

28:57.637 --> 29:00.939
And they offered him immunity,
and he didn't take it, okay?

29:05.112 --> 29:07.045
    So you're skipping town
           with him?

29:07.114 --> 29:08.313
   What do you want me to do?

29:08.382 --> 29:11.049
       He can't go to --
  He can't go to prison, man.

29:11.051 --> 29:13.519
         No, he can't.

29:14.988 --> 29:16.422
           [ Sighs ]

29:17.791 --> 29:20.526
           [ Sighs ]

29:20.594 --> 29:23.162
        I'm getting him
      out of town tonight.

29:24.598 --> 29:27.399
    I'm gonna get him set up
       down there, and...

29:27.467 --> 29:30.802
I'll be back in a couple weeks,
           all right?

29:30.871 --> 29:34.139
               ♪♪

29:34.208 --> 29:36.542
         No, you won't.

29:36.610 --> 29:40.412
 You've been trying to get away
 from us since you were a kid.

29:40.480 --> 29:42.181
           I get it.

29:45.018 --> 29:47.219
           If I could
       start over again,

29:47.287 --> 29:50.723
     a chance to be normal,
        I'd do it, too.

29:52.626 --> 29:55.427
       But I am who I am.

29:57.031 --> 29:59.898
       [ Voice breaking ]
           But you...

30:06.640 --> 30:08.807
         I'll miss you.

30:13.647 --> 30:16.882
       [ Engine starts ]

30:22.289 --> 30:25.657
      [ Breathes deeply ]

30:29.830 --> 30:31.730
             Jake:
      You're Craig, right?

30:33.567 --> 30:35.134
             Yeah.

30:36.703 --> 30:39.171
          Who are you?

30:39.239 --> 30:41.173
           I'm Jake.

30:41.241 --> 30:44.176
     Old friend of Smurf's.

30:44.244 --> 30:46.211
    Well, thanks for coming.

30:47.782 --> 30:49.682
     I wanted to meet you.

30:52.719 --> 30:56.721
     The myth, the legend.

30:56.723 --> 31:00.659
  She talked about you a lot.
   She was real proud of you.

31:00.727 --> 31:02.628
             Yeah?

31:04.130 --> 31:06.598
        What'd she say?

31:06.667 --> 31:09.335
      That you don't take
           any shit.

31:11.005 --> 31:13.205
          No surprise.

31:14.008 --> 31:15.741
     When was the last time
          you saw her?

31:16.943 --> 31:18.577
       Not too long ago.

31:22.016 --> 31:24.683
          Where'd you
         know her from?

31:24.751 --> 31:27.886
    We hung around together
      for a little while,

31:27.954 --> 31:30.489
    did some work together.

31:30.557 --> 31:33.892
I don't know if I'd call us
a couple, but, uh...

31:33.960 --> 31:36.395
      we had our moments.

31:37.898 --> 31:39.431
         What happened
          to your leg?

31:41.635 --> 31:43.968
         Smurf shot me
        in the kneecap.

31:44.038 --> 31:45.770
   Thought I stole from her.

31:45.772 --> 31:46.905
         Well, did you?

31:46.973 --> 31:49.408
         Well, it's --
       it's complicated.

31:51.512 --> 31:54.779
   Wait. So you're the Jake that
        stole the 300K from her?

31:54.849 --> 31:58.183
So you have heard of me.
It was a misunderstanding.

31:58.185 --> 32:02.054
   But that was Smurf, right?
         Shoot first...

32:02.122 --> 32:05.224
   then never ask questions,
        never apologize.

32:07.794 --> 32:09.327
             Yeah.

32:09.396 --> 32:10.595
              Yeah.

32:10.597 --> 32:12.665
          [ Chuckles ]

32:15.269 --> 32:18.136
    All right, man, well...

32:18.205 --> 32:19.872
        I gotta go home.

32:22.809 --> 32:24.142
        What's the rush?

32:24.211 --> 32:25.544
    Well, I just had a baby.

32:27.214 --> 32:29.948
              Wow.

32:30.016 --> 32:31.816
           Boy, girl?

32:31.818 --> 32:34.419
              Boy.

32:34.488 --> 32:35.420
             Nick.

32:35.422 --> 32:37.222
              Nick.

32:37.224 --> 32:39.824
           I like it.

32:39.894 --> 32:42.160
 Yeah, all right, man, well...

32:42.229 --> 32:44.096
          grab a beer.

32:44.164 --> 32:45.630
     Make yourself at home.

32:45.632 --> 32:47.833
            Thanks.

32:56.977 --> 32:59.043
        Pamela Johnson.

32:59.113 --> 33:02.114
    Hasn't lived at that address
          you gave me since '85.

33:02.182 --> 33:04.449
         I did find her
         in New Mexico.

33:04.451 --> 33:07.786
       She did some time
   for armed robbery in '83,

33:07.854 --> 33:09.388
    couple of months in '91.

33:09.456 --> 33:11.924
      She's 65 years old,
           two kids,

33:11.992 --> 33:13.658
        boy and a girl,
       Phoenix and Robin.

33:13.727 --> 33:15.193
        Birds, I guess?

33:15.262 --> 33:17.462
  Phoenix has done some time.

33:17.464 --> 33:19.063
         Robin's clean,

33:19.065 --> 33:21.733
         owns a couple of office
  buildings up in San Francisco.

33:21.802 --> 33:24.737
      I have the current address
          for Pam, phone number,

33:24.805 --> 33:28.673
        police records,
     couple of photographs.

33:28.675 --> 33:29.975
           Thank you.

33:30.744 --> 33:34.012
        So, did I pass?

33:34.080 --> 33:35.914
            You did.

33:37.618 --> 33:39.484
              Hey.

33:39.553 --> 33:41.753
     When she was arrested
            in '83,

33:41.822 --> 33:44.957
it was for a string of robberies
   she was doing with a partner.

33:45.025 --> 33:48.426
       Detectives were impressed
     with the level of planning.

33:48.495 --> 33:51.029
          Her partner
       was a white woman.

33:51.098 --> 33:53.632
      Think that might've
          been Smurf?

33:57.638 --> 33:59.838
           Could be.

34:03.644 --> 34:06.244
       Next thing I know,
   she's got the gun, right?

34:06.313 --> 34:08.781
       And she sticks it
      in the guy's mouth.

34:08.849 --> 34:12.250
    Now, the guy is -- you know,
      he's shaking, he's crying.

34:12.319 --> 34:13.786
    He's gonna piss himself.

34:13.853 --> 34:15.719
       She gets this look
         on her face --

34:15.722 --> 34:17.188
         swear to God,
  I never even saw it in bed.

34:17.257 --> 34:20.759
  That's how orgasmic she was
  about the situation, right?

34:26.000 --> 34:28.600
              Hey.

34:28.668 --> 34:31.469
          You hiding?

34:31.538 --> 34:34.206
     I don't like parties.

34:34.274 --> 34:36.341
       When is everybody
          gonna leave?

34:36.342 --> 34:37.542
           [ Sighs ]

34:37.610 --> 34:39.043
         I don't know.

34:41.415 --> 34:44.282
   So, is this your room now?

34:44.351 --> 34:45.949
              No.

34:45.952 --> 34:47.820
      You should take it.

34:47.888 --> 34:49.888
        You deserve it.

34:49.956 --> 34:52.556
     [ Cellphone vibrates ]

34:52.626 --> 34:54.693
     You need to get that?

34:54.761 --> 34:58.197
 No, it's J. He wants me to meet
      him at some bowling alley.

35:00.835 --> 35:02.735
       Maybe you should.

35:16.917 --> 35:19.151
  My brother's out of prison.

35:20.921 --> 35:22.787
             Mike?

35:22.789 --> 35:24.122
   You remember Mike, right?

35:24.191 --> 35:25.590
            Mm-hmm.

35:25.592 --> 35:26.659
           [ Sighs ]

35:26.727 --> 35:29.327
We were pulling robberies
together a couple years ago.

35:29.396 --> 35:32.097
      Convenience stores,
     shaking down dealers.

35:34.268 --> 35:36.535
        Got really dark.

35:39.005 --> 35:42.941
They offered me a reduced
sentence if I turned on him,

35:43.009 --> 35:44.643
         so I took it.

35:48.415 --> 35:51.483
But now he's back on the street,
        and he's saying

35:51.552 --> 35:54.352
   that he's going to kill me
       when he finds me.

